%S A395035 1,2,0,28,166,1244,7556,50838,330392,2217834,14959408,102346420,
%T A395035 707121818,4934693936,34738105738,246529508304,1762353205164,
%U A395035 12683158904472,91836400707618,668719858612542,4894628181505660,35997340001521430,265914520027198698
%N A395035 a(n) is the number of different ways for two particles to reach a corner of a triangular grid of side n units, starting simultaneously from the other two corners while changing direction at each grid point, such that the distance between each particle and its own starting corner is always increasing and the two particles never meet before arriving the destination.
%C A395035 Both particles move at the same constant speed along the grid lines of the triangular grid.
%C A395035 Let ABC be an equilateral triangular grid of side n containing n^2 unit equilateral triangles. X axis is defined along AB and Y axis is defined along AC such that starting point A has coordinates (0,0), finishing point B has coordinates (n,0) and C is at (0,n).
%C A395035 A grid point (x,y) on a path of the moving point P satisfies the following conditions when generating string of coordinates of grid points on a valid path.
%C A395035 x + y <= n, y <= n/2 and x^2 + y^2 + x*y should increase when moving to the next grid point. As P moves from one grid point to the next x remains unchanged or increased by 1 unit. If x does not change y should increase by 1 unit, if x increases by 1 unit y should remain unchanged or decreased by 1 unit. Any three consecutive grid points of a string cannot have same x coordinates or same y coordinates.
%C A395035 Each of P-path from A to B gives a unique Q-path from B to A and R-path from C to A by transforming a grid point (h,k) on P-path into; (n-h-k,k) on Q-path and (k,n-h-k) on R-path. A Q-path and a R-path do not meet if r-th coordinate of Q is different from r-th coordinate of R. The r-th and (r+1)-th coordinates of Q must not appear swapped in R at positions r and r+1. Paths do not need to have equal length.
%H A395035 Janaka Rodrigo, <a href="/A395035/a395035.txt">Python Code for pairs of grid paths</a>
%e A395035 n = 2 has 2 different ways of moving from the corners B,C to the corner A:
%e A395035 Grid paths from B to A:
%e A395035   Q1:{(2,0), (1,1), (0,1), (0,0)},
%e A395035   Q2:{(2,0), (1,0), (0,1), (0,0)}.
%e A395035 Grid paths from C to A:
%e A395035   R1:{(0,2), (0,1), (1,0), (0,0)},
%e A395035   R2:{(0,2), (1,1), (1,0), (0,0)}.
%e A395035 Set of valid pairs of grid paths:
%e A395035   {(Q1,R1), (Q2,R2)}
%e A395035 Therefore a(2) = 2.
%Y A395035 Cf. A394098, A394698.
%K A395035 nonn,walk,new
